                            {
                                "type": "glossary_button",
                                "text": "weak f7 square",
                                "value": "the_f_pawn",
                                "punctuation": "."
                            },
                            "\n\nBy developing both kingside minor pieces first, White is now ready to castle."
                        ],
                        "h6": {
                            "title": "Italian Game: Anti-Fried Liver Defense",
                            "description": [
                                "Black ",
                                {
                                    "type": "glossary_button",
                                    "text": "denies",
                                    "value": "area_denial"
                                },
                                " the g5 square to White by covering it with the H pawn. This prevents Ng5 as would be played in certain lines such as this ",
