        "d5": {
            "description": [
                "Black mirrors, taking the least confrontational way to ensure their own presence in the centre in response."
            ],
            "c4": {
                "title": "Queen's Gambit",
                "description": [
                    "White immediately challenges Black's central D pawn. This ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "gambit",
                        "value": "gambits"
                    },
                    " offers up ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "the C pawn",
                        "value": "using_the_c_pawn"
                    },
                    " for free, with the compensation (if Black captures it) that White may then",
                    " seize control of the centre with a move like ",
                    {
                        "type": "add_moves_button",
                        "text": "e4",
                        "value": ["dxc4", "e4"],
                        "punctuation": "."
                    },
                    "\n\nThe gambit does not permanently lose a pawn for White, as after capturing it ",
                    "Black would find that their own pawn, which is now on c4 in White's territory, is virtually impossible",
                    " to defend (White's most natural followup, e4, would also immediately threaten to retake it with the ",
                    {
                        "type": "glossary_button",
                        "text": "now-unblocked",
                        "value": "discovered_attacks"
                    },
                    " bishop)."
                ],
                "e6": {
                    "title": "Queen's Gambit Declined",
                    "description": [
                        "Rather than accepting the gambit, Black reinforces their D pawn with the E pawn, attempting to",
                        " cement their place in the centre.\nThis move limits White's ability to further encroach with e4,",
                        " by ensuring that a pawn will remain on d5 ",
                        {
                            "type": "glossary_button",
                            "text": "controlling",
                            "value": "area_denial"
                        },
                        " the e4 square even if White ",
                        {
                            "type": "add_moves_button",
                            "text": "exchanges",
                            "value": ["cxd5", "exd5"]
                        },
                        " their C pawn for it."
                    ]
                }
            }
        }
